29/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- EU Enlargement Commissioner Stefan Fuele kicks off a visit to Belgrade on Tuesday (March 29th) to discuss Serbia's efforts to join the Union. 
He is to meet with Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic, Deputy Prime Minister Bozidar Djelic, Parliament Speaker Slavica Djukic-Dejanovic, and will address the parliament.
In other news, President Boris Tadic will meet Croatian and Slovenian prime ministers Jadranka Kosor and Borut Pahor on Friday in Smederevo, his office announced on Monday. 
The talks are expected to focus on economic co-operation. 
The previous trilateral meeting was held in the Slovenian town of Ptuj. 
(RTS, Radio Free Europe - 28/03/11)
